This paper is primarily focused on the computational efficiency of training neural networks, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the design and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. 

The paper also discusses the use of different activation functions and regularization techniques, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the paper mentions the application of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI), which are both relevant sub-categories given the widespread use of neural networks in these fields.
